'''Gabriel Gabrielsen Holtsmark''' (1 February 1867 <U+2013> 1954) was a Norwegian educator, physicist and actuary.

==Personal life==
He was born in [[Asker]] as a son of farmer and mayor [[Bent Holtsmark]] and his wife Anne Elisabeth Gabrielsen.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Holtsmark, Gabriel Gabrielsen|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|editor=[[Edvard Bull, Sr.|Bull, Edvard]]; [[Anders Krogvig|Krogvig, Anders]]; [[Gerhard Gran|Gran, Gerhard]]|edition=1|first=Olaf|last=Devik|authorlink=Olaf Devik|year=1934|volume=6|pages=|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He was a brother of [[Bernt Holtsmark|Bernt]], [[Torger Holtsmark|Torger]] and Wilhelm Holtsmark. Both Bernt and Torger were prominent politicians.<ref name=lier>{{cite web|url=http://www.lier.kommune.no/liers-historie/holtsmark.htm|title=Holtsmark|publisher=Lier municipality|language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 May 2009}}</ref>

In April 1893 in Kristiania he married Margrete Weisse, and through her he was a son-in-law of professor [[Johan Peter Weisse]].<ref name=nbl/> He had two sons and three daughters; [[Johan Peter Holtsmark]] and [[Anne Holtsmark]] became professors and [[Karen Holtsmark]] became a notable painter. A third daughter Marie eventually took over the family farm Holtsmark in [[Lier, Norway|Lier]], as former owner Torger Holtsmark had no children.<ref name=lier/>

==Career==
He finished his secondary education in 1885, and took the teacher's education in 1892. He worked as a teacher from 1889 to 1901, and wrote several textbooks: ''L<U+00E6>rebog i fysik'' in 1898, ''Naturl<U+00E6>re for middelskolen'' in 1905 with [[Daniel Isaachsen]], and ''L<U+00E6>rebog i fysik for realgymnasiet og tekniske skoler'' from 1909 to 1910. From 1899 to 1901 he edited the education periodical ''Den h<U+00F8>iere skole''. From 1901 to 1902 he spent time at the [[University of W<U+00FC>rzburg]], studying under [[Wilhelm Wien]]. In 1902 Holtsmark delivered his doctoral thesis. He returned to Norway the same year, and was hired at the [[Norwegian College of Agriculture]].<ref name=nbl/>

From 1910 he was an [[actuary]] in the insurance company ''Livsforsikringsselskapet Fram''. In 1920 he became the director of the business secondary school ''Oslo Handelsgymnasium''. From 1920 to 1923 he was also a member of the [[Statens prisr<U+00E5>d|National Price Council]].<ref name=nbl/> He died in 1954.<ref name=lier/>

